    "department": "Product",
    "description": "DRYFT\n\nDryft builds intelligent systems that automate complex human decisions in manufacturing operations\n\nWe’re a small, talent-dense team with modest roots and a love for the physical world - cars, machines, planes. Our team includes graduates from Stanford, Berkeley, CDTM, TUM, winners of Stanford TreeHacks, recipients of Fulbright \u0026 Haniel scholarships, and builders of everything from robots and race cars to software with millions of downloads.\n\nWe’re backed by the founders and leaders behind Amazon, Facebook, Stripe, Applied Intuition, \u0026 others; General Catalyst \u0026 Neo, and board members of global industrial companies.\n\nToday, we’re already saving customers millions. But this is only the beginning. ERPs ran the physical world for half a century. Dryft is powering the next.\n\n\nTHE ROLE\n\nThis role is our most entrepreneurial. I no other role will you learn more about how to become a great founder, listener \u0026 builder.\n\nAs our Founding Forward Deployed Engineer, you’ll operate at the intersection of product, engineering, and operations. 50% Engineering, 50% Customer interaction.\n\n - Design the product backbone. Work hands-on with users, translate their pain into product improvements, and prototype features yourself - ideally writing production code when needed.\n\n - Turn operations into product. Every deployment becomes a blueprint for scale — you’ll transform learnings into reusable product features, data models, and playbooks that move Dryft from bespoke to productized.\n\n - Lead full-stack rollouts. Own implementations end-to-end: from scoping and onboarding to integration and training. Align IT teams, engineers, and C-level execs across Germany, the EU, and the US (10–30% travel).\n\n - Shape how Dryft scales. Work directly with the CEO \u0026 CTO to define the product DNA, build the foundation for future teams, and grow into roles like CPO or COO.\n\nThis is a high-ownership, zero-handholding role for someone who loves turning complexity into clarity and shipping solutions that just work.\n\n\nYOU\n\n - Product architect at heart. You turn ERP frustrations into intuitive features. You care deeply about UX, speed, and simplicity.\n\n - Sharp mind: You pick up new concepts extremely quickly. You listen. You remember the details - even of things you never heard about.\n\n - Systems thinker. You design processes that scale - in code, in operations, and in how people work. You think in data and automation.\n\n - Quality-obsessed. You hold yourself to a high bar, dive deep into problems, and care about getting it right - not just getting it done.\n\n - Confident communicator. You can calm an impatient exec, convince a skeptical IT leader, and still keep humor in the room.\n\n - Down-to-earth \u0026 relatable. You bond with shop-floor operators as easily as with boardroom execs.\n\n - Fluent German \u0026 English speaker. Our customers are global, and you’ll move between San Francisco, the US Midwest, Mexico and the heart of German manufacturing.\n\n\nTECH STACK\n\n - FE (TypeScript): React, Chakra UI v3, TanStack Router, TanStack Query, Vite\n\n - BE (Python): FastAPI with Pydantic v2, SQLModel, Postgres with pgvector, dagster\n\n - AI: Pydantic AI, Langfuse",
